-- NLB Bank Gets 250 Million Euros of ECB Loans, Finance Reports
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2011-12-22T07:42:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/nlb-bank-gets-250-million-euros-of-ecb-loans-finance-reports.html
Nova Ljubljanska Banka d.d.,
Slovenia’s biggest bank, received 250 million euros ($327
million) of a three-year loan at the  European Central Bank ,
which offered a record 489 billion euros to European banks,
Finance newspaper reported, citing the Slovenian bank.  The loan will be used for “portfolio maintenance and to
repay debt maturing in 2012,” the Ljubljana-based newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
